---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ImageLightbox from '../components/ImageLightbox.astro';
import createUser from '../screenshots/Create_User.PNG';
import generateJwtToken from '../screenshots/Generate_JWT_Token.PNG';
import junitTests from '../screenshots/JUnit_Tests.PNG';
import testJwtToken from '../screenshots/Test_JWT_Token.PNG';
---

<Layout title="SYP Sozialkaufhaus - Spring Boot Backend">
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6 py-12 md:py-20">
        <a href="/abaki-overview" class="mb-8 inline-flex items-center text-sm font-medium text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">
            <span class="mr-2">&larr;</span>
            Back to Portfolio
        </a>

        <article>
            <header class="mb-12">
                <h1 class="mb-4 text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl text-white">
                    SYP Sozialkaufhaus
                </h1>
                <p class="text-lg text-gray-400">
                    A Spring Boot 3.4.5 backend for an online auction platform managing items, users, and bids
                </p>
            </header>

            <section class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-8">
                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Project Overview</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        SYP Sozialkaufhaus is a school project built with Spring Boot 3.4.5 and Java 17. It's a full-featured 
                        backend API for a social marketplace platform where users can list items for auction, place bids, and track 
                        their activity. The system handles user registration, email verification, item management, bidding, and 
                        real-time WebSocket updates.
                    </p>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
                        This was a collaborative project where I contributed significantly to the business logic layer, integration testing, 
                        load testing, and operations (logging, profiles, email service). I worked with a team and managed multiple concurrent 
                        features while maintaining code quality and performance.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Core Technology Stack</h2>
                    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
                        {[
                            'Spring Boot 3.4.5',
                            'Java 17',
                            'JPA/Hibernate',
                            'MS SQL Server',
                            'Maven',
                            'JWT Authentication',
                            'Log4j2',
                            'JUnit 5',
                            'Mockito',
                            'Artillery',
                            'Postman',
                            'WebSockets'
                        ].map((tech) => (
                            <span class="rounded-full border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/10 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-indigo-300">
                                {tech}
                            </span>
                        ))}
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Key Components</h2>
                    <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Item Service:</strong> Full CRUD operations for items, bidding logic, pagination, and status management</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Sponsor Service:</strong> Sponsor management with full CRUD and pagination</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Email Service:</strong> Async email sending with HTML templates and local testing support</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Structured Logging:</strong> Log4j2 with file rotation, profiles, and observability</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Integration Testing:</strong> Comprehensive JUnit tests for services, DAOs, and controllers</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3 font-bold">→</span>
                            <span><strong>Load Testing:</strong> Artillery-based performance testing with realistic user scenarios</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Project Screenshots</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                        The most relevant Spring Boot screenshots are grouped here to give a quick visual overview of the authentication flow and test execution.
                    </p>
                    <ImageLightbox
                        images={[
                            {
                                src: createUser,
                                alt: 'Spring Boot endpoint for creating a new user',
                                caption: 'User creation endpoint in the Spring Boot application.'
                            },
                            {
                                src: generateJwtToken,
                                alt: 'Spring Boot JWT token generation example',
                                caption: 'JWT token generation flow for authenticated requests.'
                            },
                            {
                                src: junitTests,
                                alt: 'JUnit test suite for the Spring Boot project',
                                caption: 'JUnit test coverage for the authentication and security modules.'
                            },
                            {
                                src: testJwtToken,
                                alt: 'Spring Boot JWT token testing example',
                                caption: 'Verification of JWT token behavior in automated tests.'
                            }
                        ]}
                    />
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Featured Portfolio Pieces</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        Break down of the core work I contributed to this project:
                    </p>
                    <div class="space-y-3">
                        <a href="/syp-springboot-setup" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">1. Spring Boot Setup & Multi-Profile Configuration</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Project structure, Maven configuration, environment-specific profiles for development and production</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/syp-service-layer" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">2. Service Layer Architecture</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Item and Sponsor services with pagination, validation, exception handling, and business logic</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/syp-email-integration" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">3. Email Integration with Local Testing</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Spring Mail, async email sending, HTML templates, Papercut and Mailtrap integration for testing</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/syp-logging-strategy" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">4. Structured Logging with Log4j2</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Log4j2 configuration, file rotation, console output, production-ready logging patterns</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/syp-integration-testing" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">5. Integration Testing with JUnit & Spring Boot Test</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Comprehensive integration tests for services, test data setup, mocking, and fixture management</p>
                        </a>

                        <a href="/syp-load-testing" class="block p-4 rounded-lg border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-500/5 hover:bg-indigo-500/10 transition">
                            <h3 class="text-indigo-300 font-bold mb-1">6. Load Testing with Artillery</h3>
                            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">Artillery YAML scenarios, performance profiling, user creation and item bidding load tests</p>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Learning Outcomes</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        This project taught me valuable lessons about enterprise Java development:
                    </p>
                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Building scalable service layers with proper abstraction and separation of concerns</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Managing complex business logic in microservices (pagination, filtering, sorting)</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Email integration patterns and async processing for non-blocking operations</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Environment management with Spring profiles for dev/prod configurations</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Observability through structured logging and monitoring</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Testing strategies from unit tests to integration tests to load testing</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="text-indigo-400 mr-3">✓</span>
                            <span>Performance optimization and identifying bottlenecks under load</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Project Context</h2>
                    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
                        <strong>Vivify Scrum Board:</strong> The team used Vivify Scrum for sprint planning and task management, 
                        which helped coordinate work across multiple developers. <strong>Code Ownership:</strong> I primarily owned 
                        the Item and Sponsor services, testing infrastructure, and logging/profiling setup. Other team members handled 
                        authentication, picture management, and WebSocket communication.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>
</Layout>
